Understanding the Terraform State File 

Terraform uses a state file (terraform.tfstate) to keep track of the real-world resources it manages.

During terraform plan and terraform apply, it compares:

 Desired configuration (.tf files)
 Actual infrastructure

Why it matters 

• Without the state file, Terraform cannot know what already exists

• Stores resource IDs, attributes, and metadata

• Enables drift detection

• Ensures safe updates
